Date::Performance
=================
This package adds some semblance of performance to Ruby's core Date class.

To use, simply require 'date/performance' in your program:

  require 'date/performance'
  Date.new 1912, 6, 23


Documentation
-------------
Documentation should have been included with this distribution under the ./doc
directory and is also available at:

http://tomayko.com/src/date-performance


Installation / Hacking
----------------------
Installing with RubyGems:

  # gem install date-performance --source=http://tomayko.com

Bazaar is for hacking:

  $ bzr branch http://tomayko.com/src/date-performance

Tarballs and other packages are available at:

  http://tomayko.com/dist/date-performance/


Supported Systems
-----------------
Date::Performance has been tested using Ruby 1.8.6 on the following systems:

  * FreeBSD 5.4 (x86) and 6.1 (AMD64)
  * Linux / Fedora Core 6 (x86)
  * MacOS X (Intel)


